Coerce Object

Value

Object of new class.

See also

Other S4 Class Definition: bcbioRNASeq-class, colData, rowData, show, subset, updateObject

Examples

# DESeqDataSet ====
dds <- as(bcb_small, "DESeqDataSet")
#> using just counts from tximport
#> estimating size factors
#> estimating dispersions
#> gene-wise dispersion estimates
#> mean-dispersion relationship
#> final dispersion estimates
#> fitting model and testing
show(dds)
#> class: DESeqDataSet 
#> dim: 500 6 
#> metadata(1): version
#> assays(3): counts mu cooks
#> rownames(500): ENSMUSG00000056673 ENSMUSG00000068457 ...
#>   ENSMUSG00000037416 ENSMUSG00000074884
#> rowData names(17): baseMean baseVar ... deviance maxCooks
#> colnames(6): control_rep1 control_rep2 ... fa_day7_rep2 fa_day7_rep3
#> colData names(9): sampleID sampleName ... treatment sizeFactor

# RangedSummarizedExperiment ====
rse <- as(bcb_small, "RangedSummarizedExperiment")
slotNames(rse)
#> [1] "rowRanges"       "colData"         "assays"          "NAMES"          
#> [5] "elementMetadata" "metadata"       
show(rse)
#> class: RangedSummarizedExperiment 
#> dim: 500 6 
#> metadata(33): version level ... unannotatedRows subset
#> assays(5): raw tpm length rlog vst
#> rownames(500): ENSMUSG00000056673 ENSMUSG00000068457 ...
#>   ENSMUSG00000037416 ENSMUSG00000074884
#> rowData names(7): geneID geneName ... entrezID broadClass
#> colnames(6): control_rep1 control_rep2 ... fa_day7_rep2 fa_day7_rep3
#> colData names(8): sampleID sampleName ... tissue treatment

# SummarizedExperiment ====
# Coerced to RangedSummarizedExperiment first.
# Otherwise, rowData will be NULL.
se <- as(rse, "SummarizedExperiment")
slotNames(se)
#> [1] "colData"         "assays"          "NAMES"           "elementMetadata"
#> [5] "metadata"       
show(se)
#> class: SummarizedExperiment 
#> dim: 500 6 
#> metadata(33): version level ... unannotatedRows subset
#> assays(5): raw tpm length rlog vst
#> rownames(500): ENSMUSG00000056673 ENSMUSG00000068457 ...
#>   ENSMUSG00000037416 ENSMUSG00000074884
#> rowData names(7): geneID geneName ... entrezID broadClass
#> colnames(6): control_rep1 control_rep2 ... fa_day7_rep2 fa_day7_rep3
#> colData names(8): sampleID sampleName ... tissue treatment

# list ====
list <- as(bcb_small, "list")
names(list)
#> [1] "rowRanges"       "colData"         "assays"          "NAMES"          
#> [5] "elementMetadata" "metadata"
